HEADWORD: Hiberno-Celtic
<hw>Hi*ber"no-Celt"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The native
language of the Irish; that branch of the Celtic languages spoken by the
natives of Ireland. Also <xex>adj</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

